  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u2018\u0da7\u0ddd\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Tokens' for people in queues",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Power and Energy Kanchana Wijesekera stated that the people waiting in line at petrol stations are being given a 'token' with the intervention of the three forces and will be sent home after receiving fuel at the relevant petrol station.",
        "Wijesekera said that the Chief of Defense Staff, former Army Commander General Shavendra Silva had said at the recent Security Council meeting that the three forces would be deployed to obtain information from the people in the queues by giving them 'tokens'."
      ],
